1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:01,810
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:03,540
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:05,280
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:08,110
Chloe was about
to sell trade secrets...

5
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:14,190
to a rival company.

6
00:00:16,550 --> 00:00:17,560
What on earth...

7
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:25,660
If you hadn't lost your memory,

8
00:00:26,230 --> 00:00:28,370
you'd surely find
this situation unfair.

9
00:00:29,570 --> 00:00:31,400
Go on, deny it.

10
00:00:39,010 --> 00:00:41,450
Was I really about to do that?

11
00:00:41,450 --> 00:00:43,050
No, no way.

12
00:00:43,420 --> 00:00:44,980
You'd never do something like that.

13
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:49,920
Detective, Chairman Park
is framing Chloe.

14
00:00:50,020 --> 00:00:52,420
She has no reason
to do such a thing.

15
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:57,500
I think she had plenty of reason.

16
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:00,730
She was planning on
stealing the bio division...

17
00:01:02,470 --> 00:01:04,640
from our Adele Group.

18
00:01:05,070 --> 00:01:08,370
What did you just say?
Are you kidding me?

19
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:10,240
- How dare you...
- Dad.

20
00:01:10,780 --> 00:01:12,080
That's enough, Dad.

21
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:15,880
Chloe.

22
00:01:17,650 --> 00:01:19,820
I honestly don't remember,

23
00:01:21,150 --> 00:01:23,720
but if I really did that,

24
00:01:27,490 --> 00:01:28,690
I'm sorry.

25
00:01:32,130 --> 00:01:33,830
But Chloe...

26
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:37,500
Chloe.

27
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:40,100
Are you admitting to the charges?

28
00:01:41,370 --> 00:01:42,370
No.

29
00:01:43,780 --> 00:01:47,680
I have no memory, so I can
neither confirm nor deny it.

30
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:51,580
I apologized out of respect
for the chairman,

31
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:53,350
but for a police investigation,

32
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:55,820
don't you think
you'd need definitive proof?

33
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:59,020
Chairman Park,

34
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:01,030
do you have any evidence
to support your claim?

35
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:07,400
That won't be necessary.

36
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:09,970
Fortunately, no secrets
were actually leaked,

37
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:14,840
and it's too cruel to press charges
against someone with amnesia.

38
00:02:15,670 --> 00:02:18,340
So I have no intention
of filing a formal complaint.

39
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:23,280
But she will, of course,
have to leave the company.

40
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,380
Manager Kang.

41
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:33,360
(Termination
of Brand Consulting Services)

42
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,030
So in the end,

43
00:02:37,860 --> 00:02:40,230
this is about
terminating my contract.

44
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:44,140
In exchange for me
not pressing charges,

45
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:46,840
this is the least you can do.

46
00:02:46,970 --> 00:02:49,370
There's no proof
I did anything wrong,

47
00:02:51,410 --> 00:02:55,350
but I'll agree to the termination
and wrap things up here.

48
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:07,190
Jung Ran.

49
00:03:07,890 --> 00:03:11,560
Jung Ran,
you can't fall asleep out here.

50
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,870
This happens when you drink too much
on an empty stomach.

51
00:03:23,110 --> 00:03:24,940
You said you'd live in luxury...

52
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:29,050
at Park Tae Ho's side
as the lady of the Adele Group.

53
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:32,420
Instead, you're a nervous wreck
with no peace of mind.

54
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:34,090
This is no life.

55
00:03:45,460 --> 00:03:46,660
That's why...

56
00:03:48,430 --> 00:03:50,200
you would've been much happier...

57
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,940
with me than with Chairman Park.

58
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:56,470
Your hands
may have gotten calloused,

59
00:03:56,910 --> 00:03:59,110
but at least they wouldn't
be stained with blood.

60
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:04,150
Come on, don't sleep here.
Let's get you to your room.

61
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,880
Here, let go of this.
All right, up we go.

62
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:10,090
That's it. One, two, three.
There we go.

63
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:13,660
Watch your step. That's it.

64
00:04:13,890 --> 00:04:16,090
You're almost there.
Just a few steps more.

65
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:18,130
There we go.

66
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:25,670
Watch your head. There.
Lie down and stretch out your legs.

67
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,340
This breaks my heart,
it really does.

68
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:51,200
I had no idea your feelings for her
ran so deep, Mr. Song.

69
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:53,330
Excuse me?

70
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:57,400
I don't know
what you're talking about.

71
00:04:57,740 --> 00:05:02,610
You said she would've
been better off with you...

72
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:04,140
than with the chairman.

73
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:07,550
That was just...

74
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:12,420
That's just how I feel.

75
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:16,150
She doesn't feel the same way,
so don't hold this against her.

76
00:05:17,220 --> 00:05:19,020
It's completely...

77
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:23,230
a one-sided crush.

78
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:24,730
So?

79
00:05:25,530 --> 00:05:28,870
Are you just going to bottle it up
and let it end like this...

80
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:31,500
while aiding Ms. Oh...

81
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:34,970
as she keeps getting
her hands dirty?

82
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,680
What?

83
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:42,080
If you really care about her,

84
00:05:42,710 --> 00:05:45,020
and if you're truly worried
about the blood on her hands,

85
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:46,780
then you need to stop her.

86
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:51,060
Me? How am I supposed to do that?

87
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,990
Make it so she can leave
the Adele family.

88
00:05:56,260 --> 00:06:00,030
You need to convince the chairman
to cast her out.

89
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:01,870
Isn't that the only way...

90
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:05,770
to get her to leave with you,
Mr. Song?

91
00:06:05,970 --> 00:06:08,470
Convince the chairman
to cast her out?

92
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:10,910
The evidence that shows...

93
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:14,350
that Oh Jung Ran tried
to harm my son.

94
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:19,920
That will be what ends
her relationship with the chairman.

95
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:24,660
She may even choose
to leave with you.

96
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:27,630
If you really want Ms. Oh
for yourself,

97
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:32,300
then reveal the truth
about that day.

98
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:36,830
Bring me...

99
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,740
the evidence.

100
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,470
But if I do that...

101
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,080
It would ruin her life!

102
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:48,910
Chairman Park might kill her.
I can't do it.

103
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:52,020
Besides, that evidence
doesn't even exist.

104
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:55,090
Covering for her and protecting her
is what led you here.

105
00:06:57,820 --> 00:06:59,860
If you don't want
to regret this later,

106
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,130
you'd better think this through.

107
00:07:26,650 --> 00:07:29,890
Does Mr. Song really have feelings
for Oh Jung Ran?

108
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:33,860
So that's why you asked me
to look into his past.

109
00:07:34,030 --> 00:07:36,030
After what happened with Min Jun,

110
00:07:36,030 --> 00:07:38,630
I began to rethink
their relationship.

111
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:44,270
What kind of relationship involves
helping to cover up a murder?

112
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:50,140
(Personal profile)

113
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:54,710
Mr. Song has no friends, family,
or any other ties.

114
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:59,120
Unlike Manager Kang,
who's loyal to Chairman Park,

115
00:07:59,820 --> 00:08:01,590
he's not in it for the money.

116
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:05,720
And since he's not related
to Oh Jung Ran,

117
00:08:06,490 --> 00:08:09,230
I assumed his loyalty came
from a very personal reason.

118
00:08:10,390 --> 00:08:12,530
I'm a bit surprised.

119
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:17,270
With the way Oh Jung Ran treats him,
I never thought he'd fall for her.

120
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,670
And Chairman Park pays no attention
to their relationship.

121
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:24,840
I'll have to see what Chairman Park
thinks about them.

122
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:28,480
I could use their relationship
to my advantage.

123
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:32,920
Dad, did I do something wrong?

124
00:08:35,550 --> 00:08:36,550
No.

125
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:39,120
Ending the contract with Adele Group
was the right move.

126
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,590
But let's make one thing clear.

127
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:43,730
You're not the type of person
to leak confidential information.

128
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:45,330
I can personally vouch for that.

129
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:47,670
You trust me, right?

130
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:49,700
Yes.

131
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:54,710
Good. As soon as you're discharged,
let's go straight to the US.

132
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:57,210
Even with amnesia, you can
do anything you put your mind to,

133
00:08:57,540 --> 00:08:58,680
so there's no need
to be discouraged.

134
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:00,380
Come on. Okay?

135
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:02,310
Your hospital leave pass
is about to expire.

136
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:03,780
Let's go.

137
00:09:10,290 --> 00:09:11,320
Chloe.

138
00:09:12,890 --> 00:09:15,430
It seems she's definitely
lost her memory.

139
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:18,800
Yes. I think so, too.

140
00:09:19,930 --> 00:09:20,930
Good.

141
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:26,670
I've confirmed her memory loss,
and the contract is terminated.

142
00:09:29,070 --> 00:09:31,680
Now all that's left is that brat,
Park Hyun Jun.

143
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,980
(Head of Division 2, Park Hyun Jun)

144
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:48,590
As soon as Chloe is discharged,
we're going back to the US.

145
00:09:49,430 --> 00:09:52,630
I plan on wrapping up
all of our affairs here.

146
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:57,870
But not only are you incompetent,
you're letting love blind you too.

147
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,540
As for Chloe,

148
00:10:00,810 --> 00:10:04,580
I'm cutting her off from both
my company and my family for good.

149
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:08,650
You'd better give up on her
and your feelings...

150
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,550
before I get rid of you too.

151
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:19,660
(One-Way Ticket)

152
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,660
I'll leave
before you get the chance...

153
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:24,700
to throw me out, Father.

154
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:28,900
If Chloe's leaving,

155
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,740
then I'll just leave with her.

156
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,390
Is the lunchbox ready?

157
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:52,860
What on earth?
What's with that getup?

158
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:55,990
As if packing lunch wasn't enough,
you even changed your whole look.

159
00:10:56,790 --> 00:11:00,460
You really think doing all this
will make Park Min Jun fall for you?

160
00:11:00,830 --> 00:11:03,830
He will
because he's lost his memory.

161
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,100
What?

162
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:07,740
What are you going on about now?

163
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:11,840
Min Jun lost his memory
after being hit by a car.

164
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,650
He can't remember anything
after he turned 20,

165
00:11:15,410 --> 00:11:17,110
so I can start over
with a clean slate.

166
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:18,650
What did you say?

167
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:21,990
Are you saying Min Jun
is basically...

168
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:24,660
a 20-year-old again?

169
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:26,060
That's what I'm telling you.

170
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:29,590
Mom, you think I'd do this
without a plan?

171
00:11:29,930 --> 00:11:33,100
I'm dressing this way
because he likes this style.

172
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,770
This is how Baek Jin Ju,
the girl he loved,

173
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:37,570
used to dress.

174
00:11:37,670 --> 00:11:39,370
What are you talking about now?

175
00:11:39,570 --> 00:11:41,070
Park Min Jun...

176
00:11:41,310 --> 00:11:43,670
was in love with Baek Jin Ju?

177
00:11:44,780 --> 00:11:46,980
Goodness, this is unbelievable.

178
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:50,210
Hey, honey! Come here.

179
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:51,650
- Get in here, quick.
- Why?

180
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:53,450
- Over here.
- What's going on?

181
00:11:54,050 --> 00:11:58,260
Well, that Park Min Jun...

182
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,720
has amnesia.

183
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:02,260
What?

184
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,100
There's no need to be so shocked.

185
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,570
His amnesia
and his feelings for Baek Jin Ju...

186
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:10,970
both work in my favor.

187
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:17,710
My gosh, this is huge.

188
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:19,540
Good grief.

189
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:26,480
I made it myself. Go on, try it.

190
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:27,620
Sure.

191
00:12:32,190 --> 00:12:33,190
What is it?

192
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:37,190
I packed it with all your favorites.
Don't you like it?

193
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,230
No, it's not that.

194
00:12:40,930 --> 00:12:43,630
It's just that this whole situation
feels strangely familiar.

195
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:47,200
Have we ever shared
a lunch like this before?

196
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:48,270
What?

197
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:50,510
Well...

198
00:12:51,940 --> 00:12:53,880
Yes, I think we have.

199
00:12:54,610 --> 00:12:55,680
Really?

200
00:12:57,150 --> 00:13:01,550
By the way, you still
haven't answered my question.

201
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:05,860
What were we to each other?
Are you my girlfriend?

202
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:15,130
That's right. I'm your girlfriend...

203
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:27,750
You'll be discharged
after you finish your meal.

204
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:31,080
Your father wants to celebrate
with a family dinner,

205
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,820
so we need to get home in time.

206
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,080
Sure.

207
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:38,660
In that case, I'll join you
for the family dinner.

208
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:42,490
Why would you be
at the family dinner, Ms. Choi?

209
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:45,930
- Well...
- Can't I invite her?

210
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,870
She brought me this nice lunch,

211
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:51,970
and I want to repay her kindness.

212
00:13:52,570 --> 00:13:53,570
Really?

213
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:58,010
Still, that seems a bit...

214
00:13:58,010 --> 00:13:59,280
It's okay, isn't it?

215
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:02,410
Fine.

216
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:05,950
If that's what you want, Min Jun,
then go ahead.

217
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:25,500
Wait here.
I'll handle the discharge papers.

218
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:29,510
No rush, take your time.

219
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:32,510
Right, see you in a bit.

220
00:14:36,610 --> 00:14:37,620
Let's go.

221
00:14:39,450 --> 00:14:42,850
Min Jun, it's such a nice day.
Let's go wait outside.

222
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:44,920
Sure thing.

223
00:14:56,170 --> 00:14:57,170
Excuse me.

224
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:05,310
You know Park Hyun Jun, right?

225
00:15:08,380 --> 00:15:11,150
Well, I know Hyun Jun.

226
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:15,620
That must be why your name and face
felt familiar.

227
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:24,500
I'm getting discharged.
Aren't you leaving too?

228
00:15:25,830 --> 00:15:28,700
I still have a few more tests left.

229
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,400
After you're discharged,
maybe you and Hyun Jun could...

230
00:15:36,270 --> 00:15:39,810
Min Jun. How do you know her?

231
00:15:41,180 --> 00:15:43,010
Well, that's...

232
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:45,750
What's the relationship
between you two?

233
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:48,920
Can't you tell?

234
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:50,920
We're obviously a couple.

235
00:15:52,590 --> 00:15:55,230
Oh, I see.

236
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:56,730
My gosh.

237
00:15:57,730 --> 00:16:00,930
Min Jun, let's go sit over there.

238
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,970
What? Sure thing.

239
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:16,810
What is this?

240
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:18,720
The way you're dressed right now...

241
00:16:19,550 --> 00:16:22,020
doesn't really feel like you.

242
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:25,420
It looks like you're wearing...

243
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:28,190
someone else's clothes.

244
00:16:30,690 --> 00:16:33,260
That's just how it seems to me.

245
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:39,540
All right. Chloe.
That's enough. Let's go.

246
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:46,510
What was that?
Was she messing with me?

247
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:52,850
Did you see that?
I don't know how you know her,

248
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:56,590
but she's unbelievably rude
and arrogant.

249
00:17:10,270 --> 00:17:12,570
Was that her true nature all along?

250
00:17:12,870 --> 00:17:14,370
A terrifying person
who's after the bio division...

251
00:17:14,870 --> 00:17:17,370
and even Chairman Park's life.

252
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:20,540
I can't trust
everything Ms. Choi says,

253
00:17:20,940 --> 00:17:23,650
but I can't let Chloe get close
to Min Jun.

254
00:17:25,150 --> 00:17:27,250
It's best for them
to keep their distance.

255
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:32,360
This stress drinking
is going to kill me.

256
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:34,390
Oh, man.

257
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:44,600
What? What is it? What's going on?

258
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:47,700
The chairman has sent for you.

259
00:17:48,470 --> 00:17:52,080
He'd like to have a family dinner to
celebrate Mr. Min Jun's discharge.

260
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:54,280
What? He's been discharged?

261
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:56,080
A family dinner?

262
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:59,980
Yes. Please get ready and come over.

263
00:18:00,380 --> 00:18:01,390
Wait a minute.

264
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:05,020
Stop tormenting me
and just spit it out.

265
00:18:05,620 --> 00:18:07,060
What do you want from me?

266
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:08,660
Is it money?

267
00:18:09,490 --> 00:18:12,430
How much? Name your price
to keep quiet and leave.

268
00:18:15,270 --> 00:18:18,100
What I want?

269
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:20,570
Yes, go on.
What is it that you want?

270
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:26,780
It's peace in this family.

271
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:30,880
What? Peace?

272
00:18:32,220 --> 00:18:33,850
Are you playing games with me?

273
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:38,220
The peace I'm looking for
includes you too, Ms. Oh.

274
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:43,130
If you stay in line,
I won't tell the chairman.

275
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:44,930
That said,

276
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:50,100
mind your manners
and watch your tongue...

277
00:18:50,470 --> 00:18:52,370
for the sake of everyone's peace.

278
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:04,050
Hold on.
What on earth is her endgame?

279
00:19:04,380 --> 00:19:08,590
Not being able to figure her out
is driving me crazy.

280
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:15,490
My room looks almost the same.

281
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:18,860
I'm relieved
the house still feels familiar.

282
00:19:19,460 --> 00:19:22,370
Right.
You'll be able to settle in easily.

283
00:19:22,630 --> 00:19:25,170
Rest for a bit,
then come down for dinner.

284
00:19:25,470 --> 00:19:26,470
Okay.

285
00:19:57,370 --> 00:19:58,770
These look like matching watches.

286
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:02,970
But why is one of them
all burned up?

287
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:17,220
What's this? You still had these?

288
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,220
Do you know what these are?

289
00:20:21,730 --> 00:20:22,730
Of course.

290
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:25,300
They're the matching watches
I gave you.

291
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:28,000
It looks like
one of them was burned.

292
00:20:28,070 --> 00:20:30,970
Oh, that.
It got burned during a camping trip.

293
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,940
I told you to throw it out,

294
00:20:33,870 --> 00:20:35,910
but since
it was the first gift we exchanged,

295
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,940
you must've held onto it
all this time.

296
00:20:37,940 --> 00:20:39,410
Is that so?

297
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:40,840
The first gift we exchanged?

298
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,410
Just throw it away.
I'll make you a new one.

299
00:20:48,890 --> 00:20:51,520
Let's go downstairs.
Everyone's waiting.

300
00:20:51,820 --> 00:20:52,820
Okay.

301
00:21:02,870 --> 00:21:04,400
Where's Hyun Jun?

302
00:21:06,870 --> 00:21:08,210
He'll be here soon.

303
00:21:08,810 --> 00:21:12,480
On a day like today,
he should've been here already.

304
00:21:12,540 --> 00:21:14,750
You should've told us ahead of time.

305
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:17,550
This is what happens
when you call a last-minute dinner.

306
00:21:18,050 --> 00:21:20,320
I wasn't exactly in the mood
for dinner myself, you know.

307
00:21:25,890 --> 00:21:26,890
Unbelievable.

308
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:32,360
Anyway,
you went through a huge ordeal,

309
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:34,930
but the important thing
is that you're safe.

310
00:21:36,130 --> 00:21:38,800
Rest up for a few days,
then start coming into the office.

311
00:21:41,140 --> 00:21:43,670
- Honey.
- Even if the work seems unfamiliar,

312
00:21:43,670 --> 00:21:45,680
you can take it one step at a time.

313
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:49,710
Learn from your mother as you go
and give it a shot.

314
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:54,380
Think you can handle it?

315
00:21:54,890 --> 00:21:55,920
Yes.

316
00:21:57,390 --> 00:21:59,890
With your help, I'll give it a shot.

317
00:22:00,290 --> 00:22:01,290
Good.

318
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:04,590
That's Park Tae Ho's son for you.

319
00:22:04,860 --> 00:22:07,160
I'd expect nothing less
from the Adele family's eldest son.

320
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:20,480
Even with his memory loss,
he'll do great.

321
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:28,190
Ms. Choi,
are you cozying up to him again?

322
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:30,620
I guess
you're acting all friendly...

323
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:32,890
now that he's become a fool
with no memory.

324
00:22:34,990 --> 00:22:37,930
Should I remind him
how ugly things got between you two?

325
00:22:38,060 --> 00:22:39,060
Ms. Oh!

326
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,400
What do you mean by that?

327
00:22:43,430 --> 00:22:44,700
Goodness.

328
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,370
Hyun Jun, you made it.

329
00:22:48,470 --> 00:22:49,970
You brat.

330
00:22:49,970 --> 00:22:52,440
Min Jun went through so much,
and we all gathered here...

331
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:54,310
to celebrate his release
from the hospital.

332
00:22:55,150 --> 00:22:57,080
You should've been home
much earlier.

333
00:22:58,350 --> 00:22:59,580
Since everyone's here,

334
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:02,050
I want to make something
perfectly clear.

335
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:04,420
I'll...

336
00:23:05,190 --> 00:23:06,520
marry Chloe...

337
00:23:08,630 --> 00:23:10,230
and leave for the US with her.

338
00:23:11,530 --> 00:23:12,530
Son!

339
00:23:15,370 --> 00:23:16,370
What?

340
00:23:25,810 --> 00:23:28,580
You'll marry Chloe
and move to the US?

341
00:23:29,780 --> 00:23:33,350
I made it perfectly clear
that you can't marry her.

342
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:36,550
And I told you
I'm not letting her go.

343
00:23:37,650 --> 00:23:39,290
Park Hyun Jun, you!

344
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:40,660
That's enough.

345
00:23:42,190 --> 00:23:43,630
Don't you yell at my Hyun Jun.

346
00:23:44,660 --> 00:23:46,530
I can put up with you
treating me badly,

347
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,430
but I won't stand for you
mistreating my son.

348
00:23:48,770 --> 00:23:51,270
Then you should've done a better job
keeping him in line.

349
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:56,040
Marry Chloe and move to the US?
That's absurd!

350
00:23:56,540 --> 00:23:59,410
And you know darn well
why that's out of the question.

351
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:04,350
Don't make me waste my breath
and give myself a headache.

352
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:05,950
Take care of this.

353
00:24:07,580 --> 00:24:08,890
If you can't,

354
00:24:09,820 --> 00:24:12,060
I'll throw both of you
out of my house!

355
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,800
Hyun Jun, please,
just back down this once.

356
00:24:24,500 --> 00:24:26,670
You can marry anyone you want,
just not Chloe.

357
00:24:26,740 --> 00:24:27,740
No.

358
00:24:28,710 --> 00:24:30,510
Chloe is the only one for me.

359
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:34,040
We're leaving as soon
as we're ready.

360
00:24:36,050 --> 00:24:37,110
Then what about me?

361
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,520
How can I possibly live without you?

362
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,120
You're...

363
00:24:46,790 --> 00:24:49,560
my whole world,
my reason for living.

364
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:53,760
Hyun Jun.

365
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:57,130
Things are hard enough
for me already.

366
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:00,400
Can't you do this for me?

367
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:06,440
How much more of a break
do I have to give you?

368
00:25:10,380 --> 00:25:13,920
You blame me for killing someone
and for the way you've been living.

369
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:17,350
Do I have to keep letting you use me
as an excuse for everything?

370
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:19,590
Not anymore.

371
00:25:22,090 --> 00:25:24,230
You can't keep clinging to me
behind those excuses anymore.

372
00:25:25,260 --> 00:25:26,400
Just like you,

373
00:25:27,860 --> 00:25:29,800
I'm putting myself first
from now on.

374
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:05,100
That's what she gets...

375
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:08,540
for killing someone.

376
00:26:10,910 --> 00:26:12,540
My mom and Park Min Jun.

377
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:16,280
Why are they making me out
to be the bad guy?

378
00:26:19,450 --> 00:26:23,850
Why make me look petty and weak?
Why?

379
00:26:45,540 --> 00:26:47,640
(Park Tae Ho)

380
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:03,160
If you care about Ms. Oh,

381
00:27:03,730 --> 00:27:05,500
you need to make a decision quickly.

382
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:11,630
There was another scene
at dinner tonight.

383
00:27:12,870 --> 00:27:14,000
A scene?

384
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:16,140
Hyun Jun says
he's going to marry Chloe...

385
00:27:16,910 --> 00:27:18,940
and move to the US.

386
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:22,750
Hyun Jun is leaving?

387
00:27:23,150 --> 00:27:25,520
That sparked a fight
between the chairman...

388
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:27,280
and Hyun Jun.

389
00:27:30,450 --> 00:27:33,990
If Hyun Jun keeps insisting
on leaving,

390
00:27:35,090 --> 00:27:38,700
what do you think
Ms. Oh will do next?

391
00:27:42,900 --> 00:27:44,830
Would she go after Chloe?

392
00:27:46,270 --> 00:27:48,070
And if Hyun Jun finds out about it,

393
00:27:49,170 --> 00:27:50,840
what do you think will happen?

394
00:27:53,710 --> 00:27:55,850
If you keep covering for Ms. Oh
and helping her,

395
00:27:57,250 --> 00:27:58,980
someone else is going to get hurt.

396
00:28:00,180 --> 00:28:02,050
If you want to stop her
from doing more harm,

397
00:28:02,650 --> 00:28:04,190
you have to stop her now.

398
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:08,260
Find the evidence I mentioned...

399
00:28:10,290 --> 00:28:11,930
and bring it to me
as soon as you can.

400
00:28:29,910 --> 00:28:32,480
Hyun Jun, can we talk for a minute?

401
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:34,580
Can I come in?

402
00:28:36,850 --> 00:28:40,560
Hyun Jun,
can't you at least let me see you?

403
00:28:42,030 --> 00:28:45,600
Are you really going to leave us
and move to the US?

404
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,500
Hyun Jun.

405
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:53,100
He came to see Hyun Jun about this,
not Oh Jung Ran.

406
00:28:54,100 --> 00:28:56,270
Could his leaving be that upsetting?

407
00:28:56,910 --> 00:28:58,610
And he said, "us."

408
00:28:58,610 --> 00:28:59,680
Hyun Jun, please.

409
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:01,910
Without you, not only your mother,

410
00:29:02,950 --> 00:29:04,910
but I'll also...

411
00:29:14,690 --> 00:29:17,030
Sweetheart,
what are you doing out here?

412
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:19,700
My room just felt a little stuffy.

413
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:23,100
I was looking a few things up.

414
00:29:28,170 --> 00:29:30,070
The Adele Group's
ownership structure?

415
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:33,080
Why this?

416
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:36,780
I got curious after our visit
to the Adele Group.

417
00:29:37,410 --> 00:29:40,420
I looked up information
on the company,

418
00:29:41,250 --> 00:29:45,120
and I realized I'm surprisingly
comfortable with this kind of data.

419
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:49,230
I don't remember anything,
but I can understand it easily.

420
00:29:52,060 --> 00:29:54,500
It's getting late.
Go on inside and get some rest.

421
00:29:55,230 --> 00:29:56,500
Come on.

422
00:29:58,500 --> 00:29:59,500
Get some rest.

423
00:30:25,260 --> 00:30:28,530
It must've been burning hot.
How could you have been in there?

424
00:30:48,050 --> 00:30:49,490
What kind of memory is this?

425
00:31:00,130 --> 00:31:02,130
Was this the place I remembered?

426
00:31:03,670 --> 00:31:05,600
I wonder what happened here.

427
00:31:19,850 --> 00:31:20,920
Hey.

428
00:31:25,660 --> 00:31:26,920
What are you doing here?

429
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:34,000
I just felt a little cooped up.

430
00:31:35,100 --> 00:31:36,330
What about you?

431
00:31:37,870 --> 00:31:39,770
I was checking something out.

432
00:31:42,970 --> 00:31:44,110
Right. Well...

433
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:47,880
Wait.

434
00:31:51,250 --> 00:31:54,020
I'm Park Min Jun.

435
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:57,720
Next time we meet,

436
00:31:58,020 --> 00:32:00,560
just call me by my name, Chloe.

437
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:05,460
Right.

438
00:32:22,380 --> 00:32:23,410
Min Jun.

439
00:32:46,570 --> 00:32:49,640
(Pearl in Red)

440
00:32:49,940 --> 00:32:52,640
Why does Min Jun keep paying
so much attention to Chloe?

441
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:55,410
What if being around Chloe
brings back his memory?

442
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:58,950
Your insecurity is yours
to deal with.

443
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,380
Meanwhile,
my relationship with Chloe...

444
00:33:00,380 --> 00:33:02,090
is mine to handle.

445
00:33:02,190 --> 00:33:03,920
Is it twisted of me
to assume that...

446
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:05,020
- about Mr. Song and Hyun Jun?
- That's odd.

447
00:33:05,020 --> 00:33:07,290
If Mr. Song is
Hyun Jun's biological father,

448
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:09,060
it changes everything.

449
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:11,330
Please, do some more digging
on Mr. Song for me.

450
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:14,360
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
